accessibility.text: If you earn interest = inflation + 4%, your savings will last exactly 25 years…
If you earn interest = inflation, your savings will last only 16 years…
Assume you have $400,000 saved at age 65 when you retire
If you earn interest =  inflation +3%, your savings will last only 22 years…
If you earn zero interest, your savings will last only 13 years…
Those savings must last for 25 years, assuming you only live to 90
When you retire, you need at least $2,000/month or  $24,000/year to survive
